1. What is Bootstrap?
A. Bootstrap is a free, open-source framework for front-end development. It's used to create responsive websites and web apps.
   Bootstrap is the most popular CSS Framework for developing responsive and mobile-first websites, , tablets, and desktops.
   Bootstrap 5 is the newest version of Bootstrap.


2. What is a Bootstrap Container, and how does it work?
A. There are two types of containers:

The .container class creates a fixed-width container that is responsive.
The .container-fluid class creates a full-width container that spans the entire viewport width.
There are two types of containers:

• .container class creates a fixed-width container that is responsive.
• The .container-fluid class creates a full-width container that spans the entire viewport width.




























































































